  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onion and sliced celery; sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in diced carrots and potatoes and cook for another 3 minutes.",
    "Mix in 2 cups sauerkraut, tomato paste, ground cumin, and coriander; cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in 2 cups vegetable stock and 1 cup soy milk, bring to a simmer.",
    "Cover and let the stew gently simmer for 25 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.",
    "Season with salt to taste; stir well.",
    "Serve hot, optionally garnished with fresh parsley."
